‘At the time of his death, my father, Ali b. al-Husayn (a) hugged me close to his chest and said, ‘O my son! I advise you as my father advised me at the time of his death, and he proceeded to mention that his father had advised him, saying: ‘O my son! Endure the truth even if it be bitter.’
— Imam Baqir (a), Bihar al-Anwar 